# Normalise line endings so source compiles to byte-identical output on every platform.
#
# C# sources are checked out with CRLF on all platforms (matching .editorconfig's
# end_of_line = crlf). This is required for the functional-test HTTP cache: prompts are
# built from verbatim string literals (e.g. EpisodeExtractionPrompt), so their newlines
# are baked into the request body at compile time. The cache key is SHA256 of that body,
# so a CRLF/LF difference between the Windows machine that records cassettes and the Linux
# CI runner is a permanent cache miss — which forwards to the live LLM and breaks offline CI.
*.cs text eol=crlf
